The Nakuru County government has got a reprieve after the High Court lifted orders stopping collection of revenue from matatus operating town service.
In her ruling, Justice Teresia Matheka set aside the orders she had issued earlier on January 16 suspending collection of Sh2,000 monthly for seasonal tickets from each of 8,600 public service vehicles pending the hearing and determination of a case which had been filed by the operators.



